{"key":"post-8612880","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8612880</id>\n<content>I believe spore allergies are species specific.&amp;nbsp; So far, I only have one species that I'm horribly allergic to, &lt;i&gt;H ulmarius&lt;/i&gt;.&amp;nbsp; In fact, I won't even grow that one indoors anymore.&amp;nbsp; Once you get a heavy dose of spores and your immune system rejects them, you'll be allergic to that species' spores, even in very small amounts, perhaps forever.&amp;nbsp; For cubes, the answer is to pick large pins prior to the veil beginning to tear.&amp;nbsp; Besides, they're at peak quality at that time anyway. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/wink.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:wink:&quot; title=&quot;:wink:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8612900</next>\n<prev>8612850</prev>\n<first>8608146</first>\n<last>8615506</last>\n<when>1215627135</when>\n<utime>07/09/08 09:12 PM</utime>\n</post>"}